    <section>
      <h2>How They Actually Differ</h2>

      <h3>Workflow</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> You browse or get matched to jobs on the integrated board. For each job, the AI tailors your resume to match the job description. You review the tailored resume, approve it, then apply. Everything happens in one platform.</p>
      <p><strong>AI Auto Apply:</strong> You upload one resume, set job search criteria, and the tool automatically applies to matching jobs across external job boards. You have limited visibility into what's being sent.</p>

      <h3>Automation vs Manual Effort</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Automates resume tailoring and job matching, but requires you to review and approve each application. This takes 30-60 seconds per job but ensures quality.</p>
      <p><strong>AI Auto Apply:</strong> Fully automated once configured. Can apply to hundreds of jobs per day with zero manual effort, but uses the same generic resume for all.</p>

      <h3>Output Quality</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Each resume is optimized for ATS systems and matches job-specific keywords. Higher interview rates because applications are targeted.</p>
      <p><strong>AI Auto Apply:</strong> Uses one resume template for all applications. Lower interview rates in competitive markets because applications aren't customized.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Simple setup—create profile, upload resume, start browsing. The tailoring happens automatically; you just review and approve.</p>
      <p><strong>AI Auto Apply:</strong> Requires initial configuration of job search parameters. Once set, runs automatically but offers less control over what gets sent.</p>

      <h3>Friction Points</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Requires reviewing each tailored resume (adds 30-60 seconds per application). Free tier has credit limits for premium features.</p>
      <p><strong>AI Auto Apply:</strong> No free tier. Limited visibility into applications being sent. Risk of applying to irrelevant or scam jobs without your knowledge.</p>
